        "references": [
            "For the ASR model111The code is available at: https://github.com/augustgw/early-exit-transformer, we use the EE architecture shown in Fig. 1(b) [20]. The network takes as input 80 Mel Frequency Cepstral Coefficients (MFCCs). This sequence is passed through two depth-wise convolutional layers, each downsampling the input data by factor 222, followed by a stack of N=12\ud835\udc4112N=12 conformer layers with M=6\ud835\udc406M=6 intermediate decoders (one every 2 conformer layers, M=N2\ud835\udc40\ud835\udc412M=\\frac{N}{2}). Each exit is an independent head consisting of a linear layer. The model uses a byte pair encoding (BPE) based tokenizer [50] with 256 tokens and it is trained using the CTC loss [51, 52].\nTable 1 summarizes the main hyperparameters of the model and of the training procedure."
